Day 1-Assignment:

1) What is Python?What are different ways to install python in PC?
Ans: Python is a general-purpose, high level, object-oriented programming language.
Ways to install Python are:
i) Can be downloaded from the official website "python.org" and installed.
ii) By installing Anaconda Distribution which is bundlled up with not just python but also many other packages and libraries.

2) What are the code Environments? Types?
Ans: Code environment is a place where one can write their code, compile and see the outputs, all together in one place.
There are 3 types of Environment:
ii) Text Editors
ii) Full IDE
iii) Notebook Environments
